## 3. System Design and Architecture

### 3.1 Technology Stack

| Component | Technology | Justification |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend Framework | Vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript | Zero build overhead, maximum browser compatibility |
| Blockchain Layer | Custom JS Blockchain Simulator | Client-side execution, no fee/gas costs |
| Authentication | Firebase Auth | Industry-grade, free tier sufficient |
| Database | Firebase Firestore + localStorage | Hybrid persistence |
| Maps | Leaflet.js (OpenStreetMap) | Open-source, offline-capable tiles |
| Charts | Chart.js | Lightweight, canvas-based |
| QR Scanning | HTML5-QRCode | Camera API access, no native app required |
| PDF Generation | jsPDF | Client-side PDF creation |
| AI Chatbot | OpenRouter (GPT-3.5-Turbo) | LLM access via API |
| Icons | Phosphor Icons | Comprehensive icon library |
| PWA | Service Worker + manifest.json | Offline and installable |

### 3.2 Blockchain Data Architecture

The VaidyaChain blockchain is implemented as a singly-linked chain of Block objects:

```
Block_0 (Genesis)
    |
    └─▶ Block_1 (Herb Collection by Farmer Rajesh, Batch HC-1234)
           - type: "collection"
           - herbType: "Ashwagandha"
           - quantity: 50 kg
           - GPS: [22.7196°N, 75.8577°E]
           - hash: "0x3a9f..."
           - previousHash: genesis_hash
    |
    └─▶ Block_2 (Lab Test by VaidyaChain Central Lab)
           - type: "lab-test"
           - batchId: "HC-1234"
           - moisture: 8.2%
           - pesticide: 0.02 ppm (PASS)
           - heavyMetals: 0.001 ppm (PASS)
           - testResult: "pass"
           - hash: "0x7b2c..."
           - previousHash: "0x3a9f..."
    |
    └─▶ Block_3 (Manufacturing by Ayurveda Essentials)
           - type: "manufacturing"
           - productId: "PROD-5678"
           - productName: "Premium Ashwagandha Capsules"
           - expiryDate: "2027-01-15"
           - hash: "0x1d8e..."
```

### 3.3 Quality Gate Enforcement

The blockchain enforces strict quality gates through the [didBatchPassLabTests(batchId)](file:///c:/Users/phita/project10/vaidyachain/blockchain-simulator.js#130-136) function. This function:
1. Retrieves all transactions for the given `batchId`
2. Checks for a `lab-test` type transaction with `testResult === 'pass'`
3. Returns `true` only if such a record exists

The Manufacturer Dashboard calls this function before allowing any batch to be used in production. This creates an **automated, tamper-proof quality gate** that no stakeholder can bypass.

### 3.4 Role-Based Access and Dashboard Design

VaidyaChain implements role segregation through Firebase Authentication paired with a role-based UI routing system. Upon login, the [showDashboard(type)](file:///c:/Users/phita/project10/vaidyachain/app.js#13-102) function renders the appropriate role dashboard:

```javascript
// Role-based rendering
function showDashboard(type, event) {
    switch(type) {
        case 'farmer':          loadFarmerDashboard(); break;
        case 'lab':             loadLabDashboard(); break;
        case 'manufacturer':    loadManufacturerDashboard(); break;
        case 'consumer':        loadConsumerPortal(); break;
        case 'sustainability':  loadSustainabilityDashboard(); break;
        case 'smart-contracts': loadSmartContractsDashboard(); break;
        // ... 5 more roles
    }
}
```

